<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-01-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-01-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="197" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d197">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Choate</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-01-22"><hi rend="italic">January 22,
                                1901</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>You will express to Lord Lansdowne the profound sorrow of the Government
                            and people of the United States at the death of the Queen and the deep
                            sympathy we feel with the people of the British Empire in their great
                            affliction.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>